00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:06,640
When you write a debate article, you want to convince the reader of your opinion.

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:11,360
You start from something you think is important and may need to change.

3
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:17,320
With clear and factual arguments, you want to get the reader to react and act.

4
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:23,400
The debate article is common in daily newspapers, but also in blogs.

5
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:26,080
Compared to chronicles and submissions-

6
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:30,120
-Is the debate article less personal and more factual.

7
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:34,160
Tips to consider when writing a debate article:

8
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:39,400
Try to have a brief and interesting heading that attracts the reader.

9
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:42,560
What do you want to say, change, influence?

10
00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:46,480
Make sure you have a clear thesis to start the article with.

11
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:50,280
With the help of your arguments you manage to convince the reader.

12
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:53,880
Choose the best and sort out excess.

13
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:57,200
Do you come up with a counter -argument?
 Good!

14
00:00:57,360 --> 00:01:02,280
By answering them you show that you can see things from different perspectives.

15
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:06,800
Please refer to sources to strengthen your arguments.

16
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:10,520
Don't be afraid to arouse reactions and feelings.

17
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:14,080
It is just fine.
 Then you create a commitment.

18
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:18,520
Summarize your article at the end.
 Repeat your tes-

19
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:24,400
-and use your strongest argument.
 You can also leave a call.

